<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>A global problem</strong></h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image show-tablet-desktop"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" 
     	loading="lazy" src="https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/OPAY-Spam-Call-Assets-Desktop-04.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-186745" srcset="https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/OPAY-Spam-Call-Assets-Desktop-04.jpg 1920w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/OPAY-Spam-Call-Assets-Desktop-04-300x169.jpg 300w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/OPAY-Spam-Call-Assets-Desktop-04-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/OPAY-Spam-Call-Assets-Desktop-04-768x432.jpg 768w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/OPAY-Spam-Call-Assets-Desktop-04-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/OPAY-Spam-Call-Assets-Desktop-04-1240x698.jpg 1240w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Image source: Chima David/TechCabal</figcaption></figure>



<figure class="wp-block-image mobile-only"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1080" height="1350" 
     	loading="lazy" src="https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/OPAY-Spam-Call-Assets-04.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-186752" srcset="https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/OPAY-Spam-Call-Assets-04.jpg 1080w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/OPAY-Spam-Call-Assets-04-240x300.jpg 240w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/OPAY-Spam-Call-Assets-04-819x1024.jpg 819w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/OPAY-Spam-Call-Assets-04-768x960.jpg 768w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/OPAY-Spam-Call-Assets-04-720x900.jpg 720w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 1080px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Image source: Chima David/TechCabal</figcaption></figure>



<p>Spam call complaints are not unique to Nigeria. In several markets, financial institutions have emerged as major drivers of spam calls, prompting regulatory intervention.&nbsp;</p>



<p>In 2019, South Africans <a href="https://cbn.co.za/featured/truecaller-insights-reveals-south-africa-still-one-of-the-most-spam-plagued-countries-in-the-world/?utm_source=newsletter&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=ip-oh-no&amp;_bhlid=672e4d32e27a35cd08f37a46a918f1565de84de1" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">were one of the most spammed people in Africa.</a> At the time, people received up to <a href="https://cbn.co.za/featured/truecaller-insights-reveals-south-africa-still-one-of-the-most-spam-plagued-countries-in-the-world/?utm_source=newsletter&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=ip-oh-no&amp;_bhlid=672e4d32e27a35cd08f37a46a918f1565de84de1" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">25 spam calls monthly.</a> Spam calls in the country have persisted over the years.</p>



<p>In a September 2024 case, SBM Bank Kenya, a Kenyan commercial bank, was<a href="https://www.businessdailyafrica.com/bd/corporate/companies/sbm-bank-fined-sh0-4m-over-spam-emails-to-non-customer-4761452" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"> fined</a> Sh0.4m ($3,489) for sending hundreds of unsolicited emails to a non‑customer. In December 2025, the&nbsp; Kenyan Office of the Data Protection Commissioner (ODPC)<a href="https://nation.africa/kenya/business/platinum-credit-fined-sh400-000-for-spamming-man-with-unsolicited-smss-calls-5286538" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"> fined</a> Platinum Credit, a microfinance lending company, about Sh400,000 ($3,100) for repeatedly sending unsolicited calls and SMS to a customer.&nbsp;</p>



<p>&nbsp;In January 2026,&nbsp; South Africa’s Information Regulator <a href="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/smartphones/625404-say-goodbye-to-spam-calls-in-south-africa-3.html?utm_source=newsletter&amp;utm_medium=newsletter&amp;utm_campaign=ip-oh-no&amp;_bhlid=a2468e638119bec326c9e243e841d94f6c6b70d1" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">announced</a> that offenders can be fined up to R10 million ($624,325) or jailed.</p>



<p>Across these markets, regulators have moved to treat persistent marketing calls as a privacy issue that demands enforcement.</p>



<p>When asked what the industry standard should be, Bamaiyi pointed to traditional commercial banks as a model for ethical marketing.</p>



<p>&nbsp;&#8220;The traditional banks in Nigeria, if they want to tell you about loans, they just send it to your email. [They] would never call you to say &#8216;hey, come and take a loan from us,'&#8221; he said.</p>



<p>The filmmaker’s solution for microfinance banks and lending apps is to move the conversation to less intrusive channels.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="2560" height="28" 
     	loading="lazy" src="https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Dividerx-scaled.png" alt="" class="wp-image-186958" srcset="https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Dividerx-scaled.png 2560w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Dividerx-300x3.png 300w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Dividerx-1024x11.png 1024w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Dividerx-768x8.png 768w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Dividerx-1536x17.png 1536w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Dividerx-2048x22.png 2048w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Dividerx-1240x14.png 1240w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" /></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Is there an opt-out option?</strong></h2>



<p>The persistence of these calls may indicate that OPay’s system is failing to provide users with an easy opt-out option.</p>



<p>The technical workaround of blocking these numbers has proven futile for many. Benny, a member of Nigeria’s National Youth Service Corps, a mandatory one-year public service program for university graduates, cleared his debt only to be hounded by &#8220;upgrade&#8221; offers.&nbsp;</p>



<p>“Even when I block some of their numbers, they will use new ones to call, and it’s frustrating. They really need to stop,” he said.</p>



<p>Dosekun said that while some companies bury these permissions in the fine print of their terms and conditions and privacy policy, NDPC is pushing for transparency.</p>



<p>“On the part of data controllers and processors, we tell them to shorten their terms and conditions and privacy policy, importantly, to just make it short and precise,” he said.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="2560" height="28" 
     	loading="lazy" src="https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Dividerx-scaled.png" alt="" class="wp-image-186958" srcset="https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Dividerx-scaled.png 2560w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Dividerx-300x3.png 300w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Dividerx-1024x11.png 1024w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Dividerx-768x8.png 768w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Dividerx-1536x17.png 1536w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Dividerx-2048x22.png 2048w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Dividerx-1240x14.png 1240w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" /></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Unregulated market?</strong></h2>



<p>For companies that fail to rein in these practices, the penalties go beyond simple warnings. Dosekun warned that the NDPC can penalise non-compliant firms.&nbsp;</p>



<p>“The NDPC has the power to fine these organisations. The fine can even go from ₦10 million ($7,027) to 2% of your gross earnings in the past year,” he said. The consequences can even escalate beyond the company&#8217;s balance sheet: “It can even go as far as jail time for the CEO of the organisation.”</p>



<p>Despite the NDPC’s warnings and the Federal Competition and Consumer Protection Commission (FCCPC) efforts to <a href="https://www.mondaq.com/nigeria/dodd-frank-consumer-protection-act/1708234/the-federal-competition-and-consumer-protection-commission-sets-deadline-for-registration-of-digital-lenders">clamp down</a> on digital debt collectors, the line between marketing and harassment remains thin.&nbsp;</p>



<p>For Winsome Charles, an Abuja-based teacher, that line was crossed long ago.</p>



<p>“I have removed the SIM [card] I used to open the OPay account because I got tired of the calls. It was really becoming a problem,” she said.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image show-tablet-desktop"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="2560" height="1440" 
     	loading="lazy" src="https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Web-Quote-Charles-scaled.png" alt="" class="wp-image-186991" srcset="https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Web-Quote-Charles-scaled.png 2560w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Web-Quote-Charles-300x169.png 300w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Web-Quote-Charles-1024x576.png 1024w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Web-Quote-Charles-768x432.png 768w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Web-Quote-Charles-1536x864.png 1536w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Web-Quote-Charles-2048x1152.png 2048w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Web-Quote-Charles-1240x698.png 1240w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" /></figure>



<figure class="wp-block-image mobile-only"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="2160" height="2560" 
     	loading="lazy" src="https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Quote-Charles.png" alt="" class="wp-image-186996" srcset="https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Quote-Charles.png 2160w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Quote-Charles-253x300.png 253w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Quote-Charles-864x1024.png 864w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Quote-Charles-768x910.png 768w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Quote-Charles-1296x1536.png 1296w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Quote-Charles-1728x2048.png 1728w, https://c76c7bbc41.mjedge.net/wp-content/uploads/tc/2026/04/Quote-Charles-759x900.png 759w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2160px) 100vw, 2160px" /></figure>



